## 2. TECH STACK RULES

- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router)
- **Auth & DB:** Supabase â€” always use the Supabase client, never bypass RLS
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS only â€” no inline styles, no CSS modules unless absolutely necessary
- **Language:** TypeScript throughout â€” no `any` types
- **State:** React hooks (useState, useEffect, useContext) â€” no Redux
- **Forms:** Controlled components â€” never use HTML `<form>` submit
- **Images/Camera:** Native browser APIs + Tesseract.js for OCR
- **Notifications:** Supabase Realtime or browser push API
- **Deployment:** Vercel â€” ensure all env vars use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for client-side

---

## 3. BRAND & UI STANDARDS

- **Primary colour:** Navy blue (`#1a2744`)
- **Accent colour:** Gold (`#c9a84c`)
- **Background:** Dark navy on mobile mechanic screens; white/light grey on desktop supervisor screens
- **Font:** Clean, readable sans-serif â€” mechanic screens must be large-tap-target friendly
- **Mobile-first:** All mechanic screens (M-01 to M-11) are mobile-first PWA screens
- **Desktop-first:** All supervisor, OPS, and admin screens are desktop-first
- **Buttons:** Large, high-contrast, full-width on mobile â€” never small tap targets for mechanics
- **Hard gate screens:** Display a prominent RED banner/block when a control gate is enforced

---

## 4. USER ROLES & ROUTING

There are four roles. Each role has its own protected route namespace.

| Role | Route Prefix | Primary Interface |
|---|---|---|
| Mechanic | `/mechanic/` | Mobile PWA |
| Workshop Manager | `/manager/` | Desktop |
| OPS Manager | `/ops/` | Desktop |
| Administrator | `/admin/` | Desktop |

**Rules:**
- After login, redirect each role to their dashboard immediately
- Use Supabase Auth with role stored in `user_metadata` or a `profiles` table
- Middleware must protect all role routes â€” a mechanic cannot access `/manager/`
- Never expose supervisor or OPS data to mechanic screens

---

## 5. THE 16-STEP JOB LIFECYCLE (AUTHORITATIVE)

This is the single source of truth for how every job progresses. Every screen maps to one or more of these steps.

| Step | Activity | Role | Interface |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Job raised, quote completed & sent to customer | Workshop Manager | Supervisor Desktop |
| 2 | Customer PO / approval received | Workshop Manager | Supervisor Desktop |
| 3 | Mechanic logs on to job | Mechanic | Mobile App |
| 4 | Mandatory safety & readiness checklist (VIN, safe environment, not blocking faster job) | Mechanic | Mobile App |
| 5 | Test vehicle & diagnose | Mechanic | Mobile App |
| 6 | Log defects with evidence & severity (Red/Orange) | Mechanic | Mobile App |
| 7 | Manager reviews defects & seeks customer approval | Workshop Manager | Supervisor Desktop |
| 8 | Parts ordered for approved defects | Workshop Manager | Supervisor Desktop |
| 9 | Additional job created for approved extra work | Workshop Manager | Supervisor Desktop |
| 10 | Mechanic completes approved additional work | Mechanic | Mobile App |
| 11 | Complete all works & test / test-drive | Mechanic | Mobile App |
| 12 | Mechanic sign-off checklist & job notes (voice or text) | Mechanic | Mobile App |
| 13 | Manager two-hand-touch review & approval | Workshop Manager | Supervisor Desktop |
| 14 | Mechanic final sign-off | Mechanic | Mobile App |
| 15 | OPS manager close-out & cost validation | OPS Manager | Supervisor Desktop |
| 16 | Final approval, invoicing & vehicle release | OPS Manager / Admin | Supervisor Desktop |

