## 10. CORE DATA MODEL

### Key Entities & Rules

**Job**
- The sole commercial and billing unit
- Must reference a PO or formal customer approval
- Can have multiple mechanics contributing labour
- Linked to one vehicle (vehicle can have multiple concurrent jobs)
- One job = one invoice = one PO

**Mechanic**
- Can only have ONE active job at any point in time (enforced hard)
- Must be clocked on (shift active) to record labour
- Can work many jobs over time (many-to-many over time)

**Vehicle**
- Is context only â€” NOT the billing unit
- Can have multiple jobs open concurrently
- Identified by VIN / Fleet Number / Radio Number

**Shift**
- Represents mechanic's working period (clock-on to clock-off)
- Clock-off auto-pauses active job

**TimeEntry**
- Always linked to: Mechanic + Job + Shift
- Immutable once job is closed or invoiced

**JobPart**
- Parts lifecycle: Requested â†’ Ordered â†’ Received â†’ Issued
- Always linked to a job â€” never free-floating

**Invoice**
- Generated per job (never per vehicle)
- Immutable once issued

### Supabase Tables (already created)
- `jobs`
- `shifts`
- `time_entries`
- `job_safety_checklists`
- `job_diagnoses`
- `job_odometer_readings`
- `job_approvals`
- `profiles` (user roles)

